  "description": [
    "SHENANDOAH HERLD SPUSLISHRD WEEKLY BY JNO 5 GRAB1LL WOUDSTOCK hi ART FRIDAY APRIL 15 1898 or ta _ SHENANDOAH HERALD SPUSLISHRD WEEKLY BY JNO 5 GRAB1LL WOUDSTOCK VIRGINIA FRIDAY APRIL 15 1898 Divested of its glamour what does war mean It means enriching the rich and impoverishing the poor it means killing the strong healthy promising young men of the country it means tear ing the poor man from his happy and contented home and converting his wife and dependent children into paupers it means parting and tears the rending cf oyous associations and the wearing of widows weeds When preachers of the gospel unite with the unthinking rabble and upon the least provocation cry for war they only demonstrate the fact that the call which they supposed came to them from a loving Savior evidently came from another source We wantno war War ie the first remedy of barbarians and the last of Christians There are othe means of settling difficulties A war brought on by our meddling with the business of others is unrighteous unholy and devilish The jingoes are spoillng for a fight but they want to choose their opponents Such powers as Russia Germany France or"
  ],
